# Lumibase AI System Instructions

## Project Identity
Name: Lumibase
Description: A Directus-inspired, Edge-native, Production-ready Headless CMS.
Core Philosophy: Multi-tenant by default, edge-first caching, config-as-code, and 1-roundtrip page hydration.

## Tech Stack
- Monorepo: Turborepo, pnpm.
- Backend (CMS API): Hono.js, Cloudflare Workers.
- Database: PostgreSQL (via Cloudflare Hyperdrive), Drizzle ORM.
- Storage: Cloudflare R2.
- Authentication: Logto (OIDC).
- Email: Resend + React Email.
- Frontend (Demo/Client): Next.js 14+ (App Router), TailwindCSS, Shadcn UI, CVA.

## STRICT ARCHITECTURAL RULES (CRITICAL)

### 1. Database & IDs
- NEVER use Auto-increment/Serial IDs. 
- MUST use `nanoid` (string, length 11-21) for all Primary Keys to prevent collision across environments.
- ALL domain tables MUST include a `site_id` (nanoid) column for Multi-tenancy.
- Use `JSONB` for dynamic fields, UI configurations, and AI Contexts.

### 2. Multi-tenancy & Permissions
- All Database queries MUST be scoped by `site_id` (Row-Level Security concept applied at the ORM/Query level).
- Permissions are defined as Config-as-Code. Do not rely solely on DB rows for core system roles.

### 3. API Design (The 1-Roundtrip Rule)
- For frontend rendering, prioritize the Hydration Pattern.
- Endpoint `/api/v1/deliver/page/:slug` MUST return aggregated JSON containing BOTH Page Layout Config AND populated Collection Data.
- Standardize response formats.

### 4. Caching & Edge
- Use Cloudflare KV for caching Configurations and Permissions.
- Implement Tag-based cache invalidation. When an item updates, emit a webhook to invalidate Next.js tags (`revalidateTag`).

### 5. Frontend & UI
- Parse CMS HTML content using `html-react-parser`. Always replace `<a>` with Next.js `<Link>` and `<img>` with Next.js `<Image>`.
- Use `class-variance-authority` (cva) and `tailwind-merge` to handle UI configurations sent from the CMS. Do NOT generate raw arbitrary Tailwind classes from the backend unless injected as CSS variables.